%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20former%20senior%20leader%20at%20Amazon.%20Mentorships%20can%20be%20a%20waste%20of%20everyone's%20time%20unless%20you%20do%20it%20right%20%E2%80%94%20here's%20how.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221559%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Brandon%20Southern%20headshot%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c81310cf0778001967ef22%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221169%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBrandon%20Southern%20says%20mentees%20should%20have%20specific%20goals.%3Cp%3EBrandon%20Southern%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBrandon%20Southern%20is%20the%20former%20head%20of%20analytics%20at%20eBay%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20GameStop.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHe%20writes%20that%20many%20want%20membership%20but%20most%20don't%20get%20value%20from%20their%20mentor%2Fmentee%20relationships.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESouthern%20advises%20mentees%20to%20do%20their%20homework%20to%20find%20success.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20had%20the%20opportunity%20to%20mentor%20several%20people%20during%20my%2020-year%20career%20in%20tech%20as%20a%20senior%20leader%20at%20companies%20like%20Amazon%20and%20eBay.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20learned%20there%20is%20a%20right%20way%20to%20build%20a%20mentor%2Fmentee%20relationship.%20The%20alternative%20way%20leaves%20mentees%20frustrated%20in%20their%20lack%20of%20improvement%20and%20mentors%20feeling%20like%20they%20wasted%20their%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20mentorship%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20this%20way.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20last%20team%20survey%20at%20Amazon%2C%20approximately%2080%25%20of%20my%20team%20expressed%20a%20desire%20to%20have%20a%20mentor%2C%20and%20half%20of%20the%20team%20members%20had%20received%20mentorship%20in%20the%20past.%20But%20what%20stuck%20out%20to%20me%20is%20that%20when%20I%20asked%20about%20the%20progress%20and%20benefits%20that%20team%20members%20received%20from%20past%20mentorship%2C%20I%20found%20that%20most%20didn't%20get%20a%20lot%20of%20value.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20most%20mentorships%20weren't%20set%20up%20for%20success%2C%20and%20mentees%20didn't%20do%20the%20necessary%20homework%20to%20make%20it%20worth%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20right%20planning%20and%20effort%20are%20applied%2C%20mentorship%20can%20fast-track%20your%20development%20and%20career.%20But%20to%20achieve%20success%2C%20you'll%20want%20to%20follow%20these%208%20steps.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%3Cstrong%3EDefine%20where%20you%20want%20to%20be%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20most%20critical%20step.%20To%20start%20your%20mentorship%20off%20right%2C%20come%20prepared%20with%20specific%2C%20time-based%20goals%20for%20what%20you'd%20like%20to%20accomplish.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20mentees%20come%20into%20a%20mentorship%20without%20a%20specific%20goal%2C%20possibly%20stating%20they%20want%20to%20get%20a%20promotion%2C%20raise%2C%20or%20better%20title.%20Other%20times%20the%20mentee%20doesn't%20really%20know%20what%20they%20want%20to%20gain%20from%20the%20mentorship.%20They%20just%20want%20to%20talk%20with%20someone%20higher%20up%20on%20the%20corporate%20ladder.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20of%20these%20things%20are%20not%20specific%20or%20setting%20the%20mentee%20up%20for%20success.%20Without%20knowing%20why%20you%20want%20a%20promotion%2C%20what%20the%20promotion%20duties%20look%20like%2C%20and%20when%20you%20want%20to%20achieve%20a%20promotion%2C%20your%20mentor%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20give%20the%20specific%20feedback%20you%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20may%20receive%20random%20tidbits%20of%20advice%2C%20but%20it%20probably%20won't%20be%20aligned%20with%20your%20goals%2C%20which%20will%20likely%20leave%20you%20feeling%20frustrated%20with%20the%20lack%20of%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Identify%20where%20you%20stand%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20must%20seek%20candid%20feedback%20about%20your%20skills%2C%20abilities%2C%20and%20knowledge%20and%20define%20your%20position.%20Some%20details%20may%20be%20obvious%2C%20such%20as%20your%20current%20title%20and%20years%20of%20experience.%20But%20other%20details%20may%20not%20be%20as%20obvious.%20For%20example%2C%20you%20may%20see%20yourself%20as%20an%20expert%20communicator%2C%20but%20your%20peers%20and%20employee%20review%20may%20paint%20a%20different%20picture.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20where%20self-awareness%20and%20open-mindedness%20are%20key.%20Without%20proper%20feedback%2C%20you%20may%20overlook%20critical%20gaps%20in%20your%20skillset%20that%20you%20need%20to%20work%20on%20with%20your%20mentor.%20Unfortunately%2C%20many%20people%20become%20defensive%20when%20receiving%20critical%20feedback%2C%20which%20blocks%20their%20ability%20to%20accept%20the%20advice%20and%20guidance%20of%20a%20mentor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Find%20a%20mentor%20who%20is%20aligned%20with%20your%20next%20goal%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20clear%20goals%20and%20general%20knowledge%20of%20what%20you'd%20like%20to%20improve%2C%20you%20can%20find%20a%20mentor%20that%20is%20aligned%20with%20your%20needs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20if%20you're%20looking%20to%20get%20promoted%20in%20a%20technical%20role%2C%20you%20may%20select%20a%20leader%20at%20your%20company%20who%20can%20influence%20the%20promotion%20process.%C2%A0But%20if%20the%20prerequisite%20for%20a%20promotion%20is%20strong%20technical%20skills%20that%20you're%20lacking%20today%2C%20this%20leader%20may%20or%20may%20not%20be%20the%20best%20mentor.%20The%20reverse%20is%20also%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20select%20a%20mentor%20that%20is%20at%20your%20current%20pay%20grade%20or%20far%20removed%20from%20your%20team%2C%20this%20mentor%20may%20be%20able%20to%20help%20you%20increase%20your%20technical%20skills%2C%20but%20they%20may%20lack%20the%20ability%20to%20influence%20the%20promotion%20process.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20possible%20to%20find%20a%20mentor%20that%20can%20help%20you%20in%20both%20areas%2C%20you%20may%20find%20yourself%20needing%20multiple%20mentors%20as%20you%20progress%20on%20your%20journey.%20The%20key%20is%20to%20prioritize%20your%20goals%20and%20growth%20opportunities.%20You%20want%20to%20avoid%20taking%20on%20too%20many%20tasks%20or%20trying%20to%20work%20with%20too%20many%20mentors%20at%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Make%20sure%20your%20mentor%20is%20invested%2C%20too%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20choose%20a%20mentor%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20choose%20one%20that%20is%20vested%20in%20you.%20I've%20seen%20many%20coworkers%20offer%20their%20time%20for%20mentorships%2C%20but%20many%20of%20them%20aren't%20truly%20invested%20in%20the%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20good%20mentor%20will%20understand%20your%20goals%20and%20constantly%20be%20focused%20on%20helping%20you%20accomplish%20your%20goals%20on%20your%20timeline.%20They'll%20come%20to%20the%20meeting%20prepared%20by%20reviewing%20what%20you%20discussed%20in%20your%20last%20meeting%20and%20what%20your%20action%20items%20were.%20Also%2C%20they'll%20review%20your%20progress%20since%20this%20last%20meeting%20to%20help%20you%20address%20new%20problems%20and%20ensure%20that%20you've%20been%20making%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20more%20common%20mentor%20relationship%20or%20a%20bad%20mentorship%20usually%20feels%20like%20a%20basic%20conversation.%20The%20mentee%20shows%20up%20to%20the%20meeting%20without%20an%20agenda%20and%20since%20there%20were%20no%20action%20items%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20previous%20meeting%2C%20there's%20no%20progress%20to%20discuss.%20Instead%2C%20the%20mentor%20answers%20a%20few%20random%20questions%20or%20talks%20about%20whatever%20is%20top%20of%20mind%20for%20the%20mentor.%20Rarely%20is%20this%20aligned%20with%20the%20goals%20of%20the%20mentee%2C%20and%20it's%20certainly%20not%20a%20focused%20approach%20to%20helping%20the%20mentee%20accomplish%20their%20goals%2C%20on%20their%20timeline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Find%20the%20opportunities%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20you%20and%20your%20mentor%20have%20discussed%20your%20goals%20and%20the%20items%20that%20you%20need%20to%20improve%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20find%20the%20right%20opportunities%20that%20will%20allow%20you%20to%20improve.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20you%20need%20to%20gain%20experience%20with%20public%20speaking%2C%20the%20only%20way%20that%20you're%20going%20to%20get%20the%20experience%20is%20to%20get%20out%20there%20and%20speak%20in%20public.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20task%20sounds%20easy%2C%20but%20finding%20the%20right%20people%20who%20will%20give%20you%20the%20opportunity%20can%20take%20a%20bit%20of%20planning.%20This%20is%20where%20your%20mentor%20can%20offer%20ideas%20and%20point%20you%20in%20the%20right%20direction%20to%20find%20the%20opportunities%20you'll%20need%20to%20get%20involved%20with%20if%20you%20want%20to%20improve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E6.%20Come%20prepared%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20extremely%20important%20that%20you%20come%20prepared.%20I've%20seen%20a%20lot%20of%20mentorships%20where%20the%20mentee%20doesn't%20have%20action%20items%20from%20the%20end%20of%20the%20previous%20meeting.%20This%20usually%20means%20they%20won't%20have%20made%20meaningful%20progress%2C%20and%20they%20won't%20have%20those%20details%2C%20as%20well%20as%20challenges%20to%20share%20with%20their%20mentor.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20have%20a%20successful%20mentorship%2C%20you%20have%20to%20come%20prepared%20with%20an%20agenda%20based%20on%20what%20you%20intended%20to%20accomplish%20since%20the%20last%20meeting%2C%20the%20progress%20that%20you%20made%2C%20and%20any%20challenges%20or%20learnings%20that%20you%20collected%20along%20the%20way.%20Without%20this%20information%2C%20your%20mentor%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20provide%20feedback%2C%20and%20you'll%20likely%20find%20yourself%20repeating%20the%20same%20content%20as%20your%20last%20conversation%20or%20your%20conversation%20won't%20be%20focused%20on%20your%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20causes%20many%20mentorships%20to%20fizzle%20out%20because%20the%20meetings%20feel%20like%20they%20don't%20have%20a%20purpose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E7.%20Do%20the%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20grow%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20do%20some%20work.%20But%20before%20you%20start%20a%20mentorship%2C%20you%20must%20be%20prepared%20to%20invest%20your%20time.%20Many%20people%20come%20into%20a%20mentorship%20thinking%20that%20they'll%20receive%20a%20few%20quick%20tips%20and%20guidance%20from%20their%20mentor%2C%20and%20suddenly%20results%20will%20appear.%20Unfortunately%2C%20that's%20not%20the%20way%20that%20progress%20is%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20learning%20to%20play%20a%20sport%20or%20musical%20instrument%2C%20you%20will%20have%20to%20practice%20what%20you've%20learned.%20During%20your%20meeting%20with%20your%20mentor%2C%20you%20may%20receive%20tips%20and%20guidance%20on%20what%20to%20focus%20on%2C%20but%20it%20will%20be%20up%20to%20you%20to%20find%20the%20opportunities%20to%20practice%20and%20then%20put%20that%20practice%20into%20action.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20this%20practice%2C%20not%20only%20will%20you%20not%20make%20progress%2C%20but%20you'll%20end%20up%20re-hashing%20the%20same%20conversation%20from%20the%20previous%20meeting.%20This%20will%20be%20a%20waste%20of%20time%20for%20you%20and%20your%20mentor%20and%20quickly%20result%20in%20a%20frustrating%20and%20unsuccessful%20mentorship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E8.%20Assess%20and%20adjust%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELast%2C%20you'll%20need%20to%20assess%20your%20progress%20and%20adjust%20along%20the%20way.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20your%20goal%20was%20to%20get%20promoted%20in%2018%20months%2C%20you%20would%20likely%20have%20identified%20the%20core%20skills%20and%20the%20scope%20of%20work%20that%20would%20be%20required.%20But%20on%20your%20journey%2C%20you%20may%20have%20progressed%20a%20bit%20slower%20than%20anticipated%20or%20you%20received%20additional%20feedback%20in%20your%20last%20review%20that%20requires%20additional%20growth%20before%20you%20can%20get%20promoted.%C2%A0You'll%20need%20to%20take%20these%20things%20into%20consideration%20and%20adjust%20your%20timeline%20and%20focus%20areas%20accordingly.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EBrandon%20Southern%20is%20the%20former%20head%20of%20analytics%20at%20eBay%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20GameStop.%20He%20also%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40analyticsmentor%3F_t%3D8cgBuY7EINK%26amp%3B_r%3D1%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%222f2a28156d5c62be58fd479eed94edc1%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40analyticsmentor%3F_t%3D8cgBuY7EINK%26_r%3D1%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecreates%20TikToks%20about%20data%20analytics%20and%20career%20development.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-leader-of-amazon-how-to-build-succesful-mentor-relationship-8-23%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690880401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-leader-of-amazon-how-to-build-succesful-mentor-relationship-8-23%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Brandon%20Southern%20says%20that%20most%20mentorships%20aren't%20set%20up%20for%20success.%20Instead%2C%20mentee%20need%20to%20do%20their%20homework%20and%20mentors%20need%20to%20invest%20in%20the%20relationship.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Brandon%20Southern%20)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Here's%20exactly%20how%20much%20I%20made%20at%20Google%2C%20Snap%2C%20and%20Cisco%20in%20non-technical%20roles%22%2C%22co