20daily%20wage%20workers.%20These%20workers%20are%20the%20most%20unprotected%2C%20even%20among%20daily%20wagers%2C%20because%20they%20have%20the%20backing%20of%20no%20union%2C%20no%20collective%2C%20no%20government%2C%20and%20not%20even%20a%20family.%20They%20are%20alone%20in%20the%20world%2C%20with%20zero%20bargaining%20power%2C%20and%20zero%20protection.%20And%20they%20are%20hungry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20employers%20know%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENearly%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20earlier%2C%20this%20is%20where%20we%2C%20in%20the%20Karwan-e-Mohabbat%20had%20begun%20our%20food%20solidarity%20work.%20Several%20thousand%20homeless%20men%20would%20mill%20around%20our%20food%20vans%2C%20desperate%20for%20food.%20These%20were%20workers%20who%20could%20not%20even%20escape%20the%20cruelly%20locked%20down%20city%20by%20joining%20the%20epic%20worker%20exodus%20of%20millions%20in%20the%20blistering%20summer%20of%202020.%20Most%20were%20single%20homeless%20men%20who%20had%20cut%20all%20ties%20with%20their%20families.%20They%20literally%20had%20nowhere%20else%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20321px)%2085vw%2C%20321px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01125246%2FBurning-Pyres-front-cover-A.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22321%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01125246%2FBurning-Pyres-front-cover-A.jpg%20776w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01125246%2FBurning-Pyres-front-cover-A-194x300.jpg%20194w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F01125246%2FBurning-Pyres-front-cover-A-662x1024.jpg%20662w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666081%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22496%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHarsh%20Mander%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EBurning%20Pyres%2C%20Mass%20Graves%20and%20a%20State%20That%20Failed%20its%20People%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3ESpeaking%20Tiger%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20labour%20chowk%20this%20year%2C%20we%20saw%20now%20among%20them%20an%20even%20more%20aggravated%20desperation%20for%20work%2C%20any%20work%2C%20on%20any%20terms.%20Whenever%20a%20car%20or%20van%20would%20drive%20up%20to%20recruit%20workers%2C%20in%20no%20time%20fifty%20or%20a%20hundred%20workers%20would%20gather%20around%20them.%20Earlier%2C%20before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20a%20certain%20unwritten%20moral%20code%20prevailed%20among%20these%20dispossessed%20homeless%20workers.%20They%20would%20not%20undercut%20each%20other%3A%20they%20would%20not%20compete%20when%20employers%20came%20looking%20for%20casual%20workers.%20But%20jobs%20had%20become%20so%20scarce%20and%20their%20hunger%20so%20debilitating%20that%20this%20moral%20code%20of%20the%20destitute%20had%20crumbled.%20The%20employer%20would%20offer%20wages%20well%20below%20the%20market%20rate%20and%20pick%20some%20men%2C%20but%20others%20would%20push%20forward%2C%20offering%20to%20work%20for%20even%20less.%20The%20rule%20that%20prevailed%2C%20as%20one%20worker%20said%20to%20us%20wryly%2C%20was%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EMehnat%20zyada%2C%20mazdoori%20kam%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%E2%80%94meaning%20more%20hard%20work%20for%20less%20wages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20dynamics%20had%20thus%20changed%20noticeably%20after%20the%20waves%20of%20lockdowns%3A%20the%20employer%20was%20even%20more%20powerful%2C%20and%20the%20worker%20even%20more%20powerless%20than%20ever%20before.%20A%20worker%20explained%20their%20predicament%20to%20us%3A%20%E2%80%98We%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20rupee%20in%20our%20pockets.%20We%20have%20to%20eat%20if%20we%20have%20to%20survive.%20We%20are%20not%20getting%20any%20work.%20So%20whatever%20work%20we%20get%2C%20on%20whatever%20terms%2C%20we%20go.%E2%80%99%20He%20went%20on%2C%20%E2%80%98Today%2C%20we%20have%20reached%20a%20stage%20when%20we%20know%20that%20only%205%25%20of%20those%20who%20pick%20us%20up%20for%20work%20will%20treat%20us%20well%20and%20pay%20our%20wages.%20The%20rest%20do%20not.%20We%20know%20that%2C%20but%20what%20can%20we%20do%3F%20We%20still%20have%20to%20go%20with%20whoever%20picks%20us%20up.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20result%20of%20this%20desperation%20of%20theirs%20has%20been%20the%20steep%20revival%20of%20criminal%20and%20brutal%20bonded%20labour.%20A%20white-haired%20worker%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98They%20took%20me%20into%20a%20village%20in%20Gurgaon.%20A%20lot%20of%20the%20time%2C%20I%20was%20in%20chains.%20I%20worked%20for%202%20months%20and%2017%20days.%20I%20returned%20to%20Delhi%20with%20no%20money%2C%20only%20with%20the%20bruises%20I%20got%20from%20the%20beatings.%20They%20did%20not%20pay%20us%20any%20wages%3B%20they%20said%20they%20would%20settle%20our%20accounts%20only%20when%20they%20chose%20to%20set%20us%20free.%20One%20worker%20helped%20me%20escape%20one%20night.%20And%20so%20it%20is%20that%20I%20am%20back%20here%2C%20with%20empty%20pockets%2C%20again%20looking%20for%20work%2C%20any%20work%2C%20anywhere.%E2%80%99%20Many%20workers%20repeated%20versions%20of%20this%20same%20story.%20Another%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98I%20was%20hired%20for%20three%20months%2C%20but%20they%20forced%20me%20to%20stay%20with%20them%20for%20one%20year%20and%20two%20months.%20They%20paid%20me%20nothing.%20Whenever%20I%20asked%20them%20for%20my%20wages%2C%20they%20showed%20me%20instead%20their%20rifle.%20I%20just%20had%20to%20run%20away.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20was%20the%20same%20in%20labour%20chowks%20around%20the%20country.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Ffrom-market-to-labour-chowk-fear-of-covid-and-lockdown-7311492%2F%5C%22%3EDipankar%20Ghose%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20similar%20desperation%20among%20the%20500-odd%20people%20waiting%20for%20work%20in%20Dubey%20ka%20padao%2C%20the%20largest%20labour%20chowk%20in%20Aligarh.%20%E2%80%98We%20sit%20here%20from%205%20am%20to%2011%20am%20%5Bafter%20which%5D%20the%20police%20shoo%20us%20away.%20But%20these%20days%2C%20barely%2020%20get%20work%20in%20a%20day%2C%E2%80%99%20casual%20worker%20Mohammad%20Shahid%20told%20him.%20Wages%20too%20had%20fallen%20from%20Rs%20400-500%20to%20Rs%20100-150.%20The%20second%20wave%20was%20still%20raging%20then.%20%E2%80%98Earlier%2C%20we%20got%20jobs%20as%20labourers%20at%20construction%20sites.%20Now%2C%20rich%20people%20come%20in%20their%20cars%20and%20take%20us%20to%20lift%20the%20bodies%20of%20their%20family%20members.%20They%20are%20too%20scared%20to%20touch%20the%20bodies%20because%20of%20corona.%20But%20we%20have%20families%20to%20feed%2C%E2%80%99%20said%20Shahid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20368px)%2085vw%2C%20368px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2F17085338%2Faa-Cover-p9q5co22nq0kstmevpte21sh73-20191227023235.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22368%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2F17085338%2Faa-Cover-p9q5co22nq0kstmevpte21sh73-20191227023235.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2F17085338%2Faa-Cover-p9q5co22nq0kstmevpte21sh73-20191227023235-300x168.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2F17085338%2Faa-Cover-p9q5co22nq0kstmevpte21sh73-20191227023235-1024x573.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-552557%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22206%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHarsh%20Mander.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Lockdown%E2%80%99%20was%20the%20one%20word%2C%20Ghose%20reported%20from%20Aligarh%2C%20that%20generated%20more%20fear%20than%20Covid-19.%20%E2%80%98Please%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20get%20another%20lockdown%20imposed.%20We%20can%20fight%20Covid%2C%20but%20not%20starvation%2C%E2%80%99%20Narayan%20Das%2C%20a%20vegetable%20vendor%20begged%20him.%20Das%20called%20out%20to%20customers%20loudly%2C%20his%20mask%20around%20his%20chin.%20He%20was%20not%20unaware%20of%20the%20risks%20that%20he%20was%20taking%3B%20on%20the%20contrary%2C%20he%20was%20terrified%20that%20he%20could%20die%20from%20Covid-19.%20%E2%80%98But%20I%20have%20a%20wife%20and%20children%20at%20home.%20I%20have%20to%20work%20for%20them%2C%20and%20I%20fear%20a%20lockdown%20will%20destroy%20us.%20They%20say%20wear%20masks.%20Do%20they%20know%20how%20difficult%20it%20is%20to%20shout%20for%20our%20customers%20with%20a%20mask%3F%20That%20we%20stand%20in%20the%20heat%20for%20six%20hours%20in%20the%20day%20when%20it%20is%2040%20degrees%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20found%20that%20the%20prospects%20for%20food%20and%20work%20were%20no%20better%20in%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20slums.%20Majnu%20ka%20Tilla%20is%20a%20slum%20where%20we%20had%20distributed%20ration%20kits%20during%20the%20first%20lockdown.%20Returning%20there%20a%20year%20later%2C%20we%20asked%20slum%20residents%20if%20life%20was%20better.%20%E2%80%98Things%20haven%E2%80%99t%20improved%20from%20last%20year%2C%E2%80%99%20was%20the%20recurring%2C%20disconsolate%20answer%20we%20got.%20There%20was%20no%20work%2C%20no%20water%2C%20no%20help.%20Many%20of%20them%20used%20to%20earn%20their%20living%20by%20selling%20their%20wares%20from%20house%20to%20house%2C%20but%20now%20the%20police%20often%20beat%20them%20back%20with%20their%20batons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20vendors%20earned%20sometimes%20one%2C%20sometimes%20two%20hundred%20rupees%20a%20day.%20Sometimes%20not%20even%20that.%20When%20they%20took%20their%20wares%20into%20residential%20colonies%2C%20some%20residents%20would%20ask%20them%20to%20show%20their%20Aadhaar%20card.%20How%20do%20we%20know%2C%20went%20the%20justification%20they%20offered%20for%20doing%20so%2C%20that%20you%20are%20not%20from%20Pakistan%3F%20(It%20was%20a%20thin%20code%20for%20being%20Muslim.)%20Many%20were%20therefore%20lining%20up%20to%20get%20their%20Aadhaar%20cards%20made.%20But%20officials%2C%20they%20said%2C%20were%20frequently%20rude%20to%20them.%20And%20they%20had%20no%20papers%20to%20prove%20who%20they%20were%2C%20that%20they%20belonged%20anywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20people%2C%20they%20reported%2C%20came%20like%20us%20during%20the%20lockdowns%20and%20gave%20them%20ration%20kits.%20%E2%80%98They%20would%20say%20the%20kit%20was%20enough%20to%20last%20us%2010%20days.%20We%20would%20try%20to%20stretch%20it%20to%2012%2C%20even%2015%20days.%20But%20what%20after%20that%3F%20And%20we%20needed%20more%20than%20just%20rations.%20Water%2C%20cooking%20gas%2C%20medical%20help.%20How%20do%20we%20get%20this%3F%E2%80%99%20They%20were%20ashamed%20that%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20they%20had%20been%20reduced%20to%20sending%20their%20children%20to%20eat%20free%20charity%20meals%20at%20the%20gurudwaras.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%2C%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20worst%20public%20health%20crisis%20in%20a%20hundred%20years%2C%20triggered%20an%20economic%20crisis%20comparable%20in%20scale%20only%20to%20the%20Great%20Depression%20of%20the%201930s.%20Informal%20workers%20were%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20worst%20hit.%20To%20cite%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fdata%2Fdata-over-12-crore-indians-lost-their-jobs-during-the-coronavirus-lockdown-in-april%2Farticle61660110.ece%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOver%2520122%2520million%2520people%2520in%2Csmall%2520traders%2520and%2520wage%252Dlabourers.%5C%22%3Ejust%20one%20figure%20from%20the%20first%20wave%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20of%20the%20122%20million%20who%20lost%20their%20jobs%20between%20April%20and%20March%202020%2C%2075%25%2C%20which%20accounted%20for%2092%20million%20jobs%2C%20were%20in%20the%20informal%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EExcerpted%20with%20permission%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3EBurning%20Pyres%2C%20Mass%20Graves%20and%20a%20State%20That%20Failed%20its%20People%3Cem%3E%20by%20Harsh%20Mander%2C%20published%20by%20Speaking%20Tiger.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690876856000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F03%2F28145332%2FWhatsApp-Image-2020-03-28-at-1.34.43-PM-1.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-many-fears-of-the-precariously-employed-during-indias-covid-19-lockdown%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Even%20after%20the%20second%20wave%2C%20vendors%20in%20Delhi's%20Majnu%20ka%20Tilla%20earned%20sometimes%20one%2C%20sometimes%20two%20hundred%20rupees%20a%20day.%20Sometimes%20not%20even%20that.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-many-fears-of-the-precariously-employed-during-indias-covid-19-lockdown%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Missed%20ITR%20Filing%20Deadline%3F%20Here's%20What%20You%20Need%20To%20Do%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EOver%206.50%20crore%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Flast-date-to-file-itr-today-here-is-what-happens-if-you-miss-the-deadline-4254374%5C%22%3Eincome%20tax%20returns%20(ITRs)%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20filed%20for%20the%20financial%20year%202023-24%20till%206%3A30%20PM%20on%20July%2031--%20the%20last%20day%20of%20tax%20filing.%20As%20expected%2C%20the%20Income%20Tax%20department%20has%20not%20announced%20any%20further%20extension%20in%20the%20window%20to%20file%20ITRs.%20Taxpayers%20who%20failed%20to%20file%20the%20return%20within%20the%20stipulated%20time%20can%20still%20file%20their%20belated%20ITR%20with%20a%20late%20fee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20a%20list%20of%20options%20available%20to%20taxpayers%20in%20case%20they%20failed%20to%20file%20the%20ITR%20on%20or%20before%20July%2031%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBelated%20ITR%20Filing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaxpayers%20can%20file%20their%20belated%20ITR%20on%20or%20before%20December%2031%20along%20with%20a%20late%20fee%20of%20Rs%205%2C000.%20In%20case%20the%20taxpayer's%20total%20income%20is%20less%20than%20Rs%205%2C00%2C000%2