%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F07%2F31%2Ftechnology%2Ftwitter-x-center-for-countering-digital-hate.html%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20blog%20post%20on%20Monday%20evening%20(August%201)%2C%20X%20Corp.%20announced%20that%20it%20had%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20the%20Center%20for%20Countering%20Digital%20Hate%20for%20%E2%80%9Cactively%20working%20to%20prevent%20free%20expression%E2%80%9D.%20The%20suit%20was%20filed%20in%20federal%20court%20in%20the%20Northern%20District%20of%20California%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20July%2020%2C%20X%20Corp.%2C%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20nonprofit%2C%20accused%20the%20organisation%20of%20making%20%E2%80%9Ca%20series%20of%20troubling%20and%20baseless%20claims%20that%20appear%20calculated%20to%20harm%20Twitter%20generally%2C%20and%20its%20digital%20advertising%20business%20specifically%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20threatened%20to%20sue%20the%20organisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre%20for%20Countering%20Digital%20Hate%20had%20published%208%20research%20papers%20examining%20hate%20speech%20on%20Twitter%20in%20June.%20One%20of%20the%20papers%20found%20that%20Twitter%20had%20taken%20no%20action%20against%2099%25%20of%20the%20100%20Twitter%20Blue%20accounts%20that%20the%20nonprofit%20had%20reported%20for%20%E2%80%9Ctweeting%20hate.%E2%80%9D%20X%20Corp%E2%80%99s%20letter%20called%20the%20research%20%E2%80%9Cfalse%2C%20misleading%20or%20both%E2%80%9D%20and%20said%20the%20organisation%20had%20used%20improper%20methodology%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20the%20letter%20said%20that%20the%20nonprofit%20was%20funded%20by%20Twitter%E2%80%99s%20competitors%20or%20foreign%20governments%20%E2%80%9Cin%20support%20of%20an%20ulterior%20agenda.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImran%20Ahmed%2C%20the%20chief%20executive%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Countering%20Digital%20Hate%2C%20told%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CElon%20Musk%E2%80%99s%20actions%20represent%20a%20brazen%20attempt%20to%20silence%20honest%20criticism%20and%20independent%20research%2C%E2%80%9D%20adding%20that%20Musk%20wanted%20to%20%E2%80%9Cstem%20the%20tide%20of%20negative%20stories%20and%20rebuild%20his%20relationship%20with%20advertisers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhmed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F07%2F31%2Ftechnology%2Ftwitter-x-center-for-countering-digital-hate.html%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20organisation%20did%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20accept%20any%20funding%20from%20tech%20companies%2C%20governments%2C%20or%20their%20affiliates.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwitter%20has%20been%20embroiled%20in%20controversy%20since%20Musk%20took%20over%20the%20platform%20in%20October%202022.%20According%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%2C%20Twitter%E2%80%99s%20advertising%20business%20has%20been%20struggling%20under%20him%20and%20ad%20revenues%20have%20taken%20a%20major%20hit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20Musk%20hired%20Linda%20Yaccarino%2C%20a%20former%20top%20advertising%20executive%20for%20NBCUniversal%2C%20to%20become%20Twitter%E2%80%99s%20chief%20executive.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690869022000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F02102823%2F46339127625_054ddd1a61_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ftwitters-parent-company-x-corp-sues-nonprofit-studying-hate-speech-on-platform%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22X%20Corp.%20had%20accused%20the%20nonprofit%20of%20%26quot%3Bmaking%20a%20series%20of%20troubling%20and%20baseless%20claims%26quot%3B%20against%20Twitter%20in%20a%20letter%20dated%20July%2020.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Ftwitters-parent-company-x-corp-sues-nonprofit-studying-hate-speech-on-platform%22%2C%