western%20researchers%20have%20created%20the%20world's%20first%20audio%20simulation%20of%20twinkling%20stars.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThey%20did%20this%20by%20converting%20simulations%20of%20gas%20waves%20produced%20inside%20stars%20into%20sound%20waves.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThey%20hope%20the%20research%20will%20help%20better%20inform%20scientists%20about%20the%20dynamics%20inside%20stars.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEver%20wonder%20if%20the%20twinkle%20of%20a%20star%20sounds%20as%20pleasant%20as%20the%20famous%20nursery%20rhyme%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20team%20of%20researchers%20took%20this%20question%20to%20the%20next%20level%20by%20creating%20a%20model%20of%20what%20it%20could%20sound%20like%20and%20the%20results%20are%20fascinating%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20little%20unsettling.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20do%20so%2C%20the%20Northwestern%20University-led%20team%20first%20created%203D%20simulations%20of%20the%20churning%20of%20gas%20that%20occurs%20deep%20within%20a%20star%2C%20similar%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finterestingengineering.com%2Fscience%2Fstages-earths-water-cycle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20convection%20on%20Earth's%20surface%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D3e976bcbf1d21b535a96c61f6c01c7dcfcc50aa961a944fe9b108d82edfb1c43%26postID%3D64c72401fa4d080252270091%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41550-023-02040-7%253Futm_medium%253Daffiliate%2526utm_source%253Dcommission_junction%2526utm_campaign%253DCONR_PF018_ECOM_GL_PHSS_ALWYS_DEEPLINK%2526utm_content%253Dtextlink%2526utm_term%253DPID100052171%2526CJEVENT%253Db888eca72f4811ee809203df0a82b82a%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20in%20Nature%20Astronomy%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20this%20movement%20of%20energy%2C%20waves%20of%20gas%C2%A0form%20and%20%26quot%3Blaunch%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20star's%20surface.%20This%20helps%20produce%20a%20slight%20%26quot%3Btwinkling%26quot%3B%20light%20effect%2C%20according%20to%20a%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurekalert.org%2Fnews-releases%2F996571%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20press%20release%20from%20Northwestern%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20then%20converted%20these%20heat-produced%20waves%20into%20sound%20waves%20%E2%80%94%20a%20process%20known%20as%20sonification%20%E2%80%94%20to%20produce%20an%20%26quot%3Beerily%20fascinating%26quot%3B%20recreation%20of%20what%20this%20flickering%20phenomenon%20should%20sound%20like.%20The%20frequencies%20of%20the%20star%20simulations%20were%20modified%20to%20reach%20a%20range%20suitable%20for%20human%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20released%20a%20sample%20of%20the%20sound.%20Anders%20described%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bjackhammer%20mixed%20with%20the%20static%20you%20hear%20between%20radio%20stations%26quot%3B%20combined%20with%20%26quot%3Ba%20siren%20and%20a%20low%2C%20oscillatory%20rumble%20behind%20it.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BThe%20more%20massive%20the%20star%2C%20the%20deeper%20(more%20bass)%20the%20sound%20of%20the%20siren%2C%20and%20the%20background%20rumble%20is%20easier%20to%20hear%2C%26quot%3B%20Anders%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22youtube%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FyqQViMPJxwE%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20we%20were%20expecting%20it%20to%20sound%20unpleasant%2C%20but%20we%20were%20surprised%20by%20the%20sounds%20we%20heard!%26quot%3B%20Evan%20Anders%2C%20who%20led%20the%20study%2C%20explained%20to%20Insider%20in%20an%20email.%20Anders%20said%20that%20converting%20the%20waves%20to%20sound%20allowed%20the%20team%20to%20understand%20%26quot%3Bhow%20strong%20the%20'siren'%20and%20'rumble'%20sounds%20were%20compared%20to%20each%20other%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20way%20that%20just%20simply%20looking%20at%20data%20points%20could%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20also%20used%20songs%20like%20%26quot%3BTwinkle%20Twinkle%2C%20Little%20Star%26quot%3B%20and%20Gustav%20Holst's%20%26quot%3BJupiter%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20modeled%20how%20they%20would%20sound%20as%20waves%20produced%20by%20small%2C%20medium%2C%20and%20large%20stars.%20Because%20the%20stars%20favored%20certain%20wavelengths%2C%20the%20smaller%20stars%20retained%20the%20higher-pitched%20parts%20of%20the%20tune%2C%20whereas%20the%20larger%20stars%20kept%20the%20low%2C%20bellowing%20noises.%20This%20experiment%20allowed%20the%20team%20to%20understand%20how%20stars%20change%20waves%20that%20move%20through%20their%20interiors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20like%20different%20instruments%20favor%20different%20pitches%20and%20resonances%20of%20waves%2C%20so%20do%20stars%2C%20and%20just%20like%20instruments%20have%20a%20timbre%2C%20the%20waves%20in%20stars%20have%20a%20timbre%2C%26quot%3B%20Anders%20said%20of%20the%20sonification%20process.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22youtube%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fpc5OJiJD2Xg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20twinkling%20effect%20portrayed%20by%20the%20models%20in%20the%20study%20differs%20from%20the%20%26quot%3Btwinkling%26quot%3B%20people%20observe%20on%20the%20ground%20due%20to%20the%20earth's%20atmosphere%20bending%20its%20light.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnders%20explained%20to%20Insider%20that%20many%20types%20of%20waves%20produce%20inherent%20twinkling%20in%20stars%20(the%20field%20of%20asteroseismology%20is%20dedicated%20to%20observing%20them).%20Still%2C%20the%20specific%20kind%20of%20waves%20produced%20by%20the%20core%20activity%20simulated%20by%20the%20team%20is%20currently%20imperceptible%20to%20the%20human%20eye.%20If%20scientists%20can%20one%20day%20observe%20this%20flickering%20with%20a%20high-powered%20telescope%2C%20it%20can%20help%20better%20inform%20of%20the%20inner%20workings%20of%20stars%2C%20gigantic%20and%20small.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20took%20three%20years%20to%20complete%20the%20research%2C%20Anders%20said%2C%20and%20he%20hopes%20that%20the%20study%20will%20give%20scientists%20a%20better%20visual%20of%20star%20cores%2C%20whose%20size%20determines%20a%20star's%20life%20cycle%20and%20where%20elements%20that%20support%20life%20are%20forged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20to%20be%20done%20to%20characterize%20all%20of%20these%20waves%2C%20but%20we%20can%20really%20learn%20a%20lot%20about%20stars%2C%20and%20stars%20are%20the%20building%20block%20of%20many%20of%20the%20structures%20we%20see%20when%20we%20look%20out%20into%20the%20universe%2C%26quot%3B%20Anders%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flisten-world-first-audio-simulation-of-a-twinkling-star-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690858358000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c72646048ff200190dc8ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flisten-world-first-audio-simulation-of-a-twinkling-star-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Northwestern%20University%20researchers%20simulated%20what%20twinkling%20stars%20could%20sound%20like%20to%20help%20study%20the%20inner%20workings%20of%20the%20glittering%20celestial%20bodies.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hgetahun%40insider.com%20(Hannah%20Getahun)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A24%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flisten-world-first-audio-simulation-of-a-twinkling-star-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22