n%20in%201971%20in%20South%20Africa.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-parents%5C%22%3EMusk's%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20Maye%20and%20Errol%2C%20who%20divorced%20in%201979.%20In%20the%201990s%2C%20he%20founded%20his%20first%20startup%2C%20Zip2%2C%20with%20his%20brother%2C%20Kimbal%2C%20and%20began%20a%20decades-long%20career%20in%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20second%20venture%2C%20online%20banking%20company%20X.com%2C%20merged%20with%20a%20startup%20of%20Peter%20Thiel's%20to%20form%20PayPal.%20When%20PayPal%20sold%20to%20eBay%20in%202002%2C%20Musk%20made%20%24165%20million.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Musk%20is%20the%20richest%20person%20in%20the%20world.%20He's%20frequently%20trading%20places%20with%20other%20billionaires%20in%20the%20ranks%2C%20but%20as%20of%20July%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-net-worth%5C%22%3EMusk's%20net%20worth%3C%2Fa%3E%20stands%20at%20%24239%20billion%2C%20putting%20him%20on%20top.%C2%A0His%20estimated%20fortune%20peaked%20at%20around%20%24340%20billion%20in%20November%202021%20as%20Tesla%20shares%20soared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETwitter%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EElon%20Musk%20started%20buying%20shares%20in%20Twitter%20in%20January%202022%20and%20initiated%20an%20acquisition%20in%20April.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdid-elon-musk-buy-twitter-acquisition-details%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%20bought%20Twitter%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%2444%20billion%20in%20October%202022%2C%20he%20had%20actually%20spent%20months%20trying%20to%20back%20out%20of%20the%20agreement.%20At%20the%20start%20of%20July%2C%20he%20sent%20a%20letter%20to%20Twitter%20purporting%20to%20terminate%20the%20acquisition.%20Twitter%20promptly%20sued%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20sale%20went%20through%2C%20Musk%20immediately%20ousted%20a%20number%20of%20Twitter%20executives%2C%20including%20its%20CEO%2C%20CFO%2C%20and%20chief%20legal%20officer.%20In%20November%2C%20Musk%20issued%20an%20ultimatum%3A%20work%20at%20an%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20hardcore%26quot%3B%20rate%20or%20accept%20a%20three-month%20severance%20package.%20He%20would%20go%20on%20to%20lay%20off%20around%2080%25%20of%20Twitter's%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter%5C%22%3EMusk's%20Twitter%3C%2Fa%3E%20verification%20changes%20were%20announced%20on%20November%201.%20He%20tweeted%20that%20Twitter's%20%26quot%3Bcurrent%20lords%20%26amp%3B%20peasants%20system%20for%20who%20has%20or%20doesn't%20have%20a%20blue%20checkmark%20is%20bullshit.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BPower%20to%20the%20people!%20Blue%20for%20%248%2Fmonth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202023%2C%20Musk%20named%20Linda%20Yaccarino%20as%20Twitter's%20new%20CEO.%20%26quot%3BLooking%20forward%20to%20working%20with%20Linda%20to%20transform%20this%20platform%20into%20X%2C%20the%20everything%20app%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20said%20in%20a%20tweet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202023%2C%20Twitter%20was%20rebranded%20to%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESpaceX%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-elon-musk%5C%22%3EMusk%20founded%20SpaceX%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202002%2C%20investing%20%24100%20million%20he%20made%20from%20the%20sale%20of%20PayPal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20nearly%20failed.%20After%20three%20unsuccessful%20launches%20between%202006%20and%202008%2C%20funding%20was%20running%20out.%20Then%2C%20on%20September%2028%2C%202008%2C%20SpaceX%20became%20the%20first%20private%20company%20to%20achieve%20a%20successful%20orbital%20launch.%20That%20same%20year%2C%20SpaceX%20received%20a%20%241.5%20billion%20NASA%20contract.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFate%20liked%20us%20that%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20told%20CNBC%20when%20reflecting%20on%20the%20events%20nine%20years%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20launches%20now%20happen%20on%20a%20fairly%20regular%20basis.%20The%20company%20publishes%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-launch%5C%22%3ESpaceX%20launch%3C%2Fa%3E%20schedule%20on%20its%20website.%20Launches%20typically%20take%20place%20at%20Cape%20Canaveral%20Space%20Force%20Base%20or%20the%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center%2C%20which%20are%20both%20in%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20runs%20the%20Starlink%20satellite%20internet%20system.%20Its%20satellites%20operate%20in%20Earth's%20lower%20orbit%2C%20decreasing%20the%20lag%20between%20when%20the%20data%20is%20transferred%20to%20the%20receiver%2C%20according%20to%20the%20company.%20Musk%20said%20he%20plans%20to%20eventually%20create%20a%20constellation%20of%20up%20to%2042%2C000%20satellites.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20launched%20its%20first%20batch%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-starlink-satellites-internet%5C%22%3EStarlink%20satellites%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202019%20and%20has%20more%20than%204%2C000%20of%20its%20satellites%20in%20orbit%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-falcon-9-launches-updates-schedule%5C%22%3ESpaceX%20Falcon%209%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20partially%20reusable%20two-stage%20rocket%2C%20is%20often%20used%20for%20launches.%20The%20Falcon%209%20family%20of%20rockets%20is%20a%20first-of-its-kind%20and%20a%20key%20asset%20for%20NASA%20in%20servicing%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20since%20the%20retirement%20of%20the%20Space%20Shuttle%20program%20in%202011.%20Apart%20from%20the%20Space%20Shuttles%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20spacefaring%20equipment%20was%20previously%20single-use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20is%20valued%20at%20almost%20%24140%20billion%20under%20Musk's%20unique%20leadership%20style.%20Because%20it's%20a%20private%20company%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-stock%5C%22%3ESpaceX%20stock%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20not%20easy%20to%20purchase%20for%20members%20of%20