tional-memory-of-the-1962-sino-indian-war%5C%22%3EThe%20India-China%20War%20of%201962%20and%20its%20Political%20After-Life%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20Indira%20Gandhi%20before%20the%20emergency%20would%20do%20it%2C%20with%20bank%20nationalisation%2C%20for%20example.%20It%20was%20a%20very%20controversial%20measure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20an%20absolute%20abdication%20of%20his%20responsibility%20as%20authority%20and%20legitimacy%20as%20prime%20minister.%20Forget%20sacking%20Biren%20Singh%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20secondary%20step.%20That%20he%20can%20do%20without%20parliament.%20That%20he%20is%20not%20even%20willing%20to%20speak%20on%20it%20in%20parliament%20and%20allow%20other%20people%20to%20listen%2C%20questioning%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20mean%2C%20yes%2C%20so%20that%20he%20needs%20a%20scene%2C%20he%20needs%20Rajnath%20Singh%2C%20he%20needs%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20he%20needs%20Om%20Birla%2C%20he%20needs%20Jagdeep%20Dhankhar%2C%20all%20to%20protect%20him%20and%20to%20preserve%20him%2C%20his%20apparently%20flawless%20and%20immaculate%20image.%20I%20mean%2C%20it%20reflects%20very%20badly%20on%20our%20democracy.%20The%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20conduct.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Let%20me%20just%20point%20out%20for%20the%20audience%20that%20bang%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20Chinese%20war%20of%201962%2C%20in%20November%20when%20the%20war%20was%20perhaps%20at%20its%20worst%2C%20from%20the%20Indian%20point%20of%20view%2C%20parliament%20was%20specifically%20convened%20at%20the%20request%20of%20the%20Opposition%20to%20discuss%20what%20was%20happening.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20what%20was%20happening%20was%20serious%20adverses%20%5Bsic%5D%20faced%20by%20the%20army%20and%20allegations%20of%20serious%20mishandling%20of%20the%20situation%20by%20the%20prime%20minister.%20All%20of%20that%20was%20discussed%20with%20Nehru%20sitting%20there%20and%20listening.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20the%20marked%20difference%20between%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20and%20the%20Chinese%20crisis%20of%201962%2C%20and%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Manipur%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20minor%20correction.%20Not%20just%20the%20war%2C%20from%20%E2%80%9859%20onwards%2C%20when%20the%20first%20incidents%20happened%20in%20Ladakh%2C%20and%20of%20course%2C%20then%20the%20Dalai%20Lama%20fled%20to%20India%20and%20the%20troubles%20escalated%2C%20he%20%5BNehru%5D%20was%20in%20parliament%20all%20through%2C%20well%20before%20the%20war%2C%20listening%20and%20debating%20and%20understanding%20what%20the%20Opposition%20had%20to%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20still%20may%20be%20culpable%20for%20what%20happened.%20I%E2%80%99m%20not%20saying%20that%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20conduct%20with%20the%20China%20crisis%20was%20%5Bblameless%5D.%20Of%20course%20it%20was%20%5Bnot%20blameless%5D%2C%20including%20his%20protection%20of%20Krishna%20Menon%2C%20which%20may%20be%20similar%20to%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20protection%20of%20Amit%20Shah%20and%20Biren%20Singh%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20was%20willing%20to%20listen%20and%20debate%2C%20and%20I%20think%20in%20that%20sense%2C%20this%20is%20deeply%20disappointing%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99d%20like%20to%20make%20it%20on%20record%20that%20the%20conduct%20of%20Om%20Birla%20and%20Jagdeep%20Dhankhar%20does%20not%20bring%20credit%20to%20their%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Let%E2%80%99s%20then%20come%20to%20the%20last%20point%20that%20you%20make%20in%20that%20article%2C%20which%20I%20want%20to%20discuss%20with%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYour%20conclusion%20is%20that%20the%20crisis%20in%20Manipur%20is%20arguably%20the%20worst%20inter-communal%20crisis%20India%20has%20faced.%20You%20write%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20you%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20situation%20in%20Manipur%20today%20is%20far%20more%20grave%20than%20that%20faced%20in%20Punjab%20in%20the%201980s%2C%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20in%20Gujarat%20in%20the%202000s.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDo%20you%20come%20to%20that%20conclusion%E2%80%A6%20Because%20three%20things%20have%20all%20happened%20simultaneously%20together%20%5Bsic%5D.%20The%20demographic%20separation%20in%20Manipur%2C%20the%20incompetence%20and%20the%20partisanship%20of%20the%20chief%20minister%2C%20and%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20blatant%20refusal%20to%20act%20the%20right%20way.%20This%20combination%20has%20made%20it%20the%20worst%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20And%20also%20the%20fact%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20border%20state.%20And%20it%E2%80%99s%20spilled%20over%20into%20other%20states.%20Of%20course%2C%20Punjab%20and%20Kashmir%20are%20also%20border%20states%2C%20but%20you%20know%E2%80%A6%20Also%20it%E2%80%99s%20%5BManipur%5D%20a%20small%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20say%2C%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20for%20example%2C%20the%20valley%20was%20troubled.%20But%20some%20remote%20districts%2C%20even%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20were%20not%20troubled.%20Jammu%20and%20Ladakh%20were%20relatively%20untouched.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Gujarat%20in%202002%2C%20some%20parts%20of%20Kutch%20and%20so%20on%20were%20not%20so%20divided%20on%20Hindu-Muslim%20lines.%20So%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20intensity%20of%20the%20conflict%20in%20a%20small%20state%20and%20how%20it%20has%20ravaged%20the%20social%20fabric%20of%20that%20state%20and%20made%20things%20so%20fragile%2C%20insecure%20in%20a%20small%20space%2C%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20border%20state%20make%20it%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F24173232%2FAhmedabad_riots1-1024x692.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F24173232%2FAhmedabad_riots1-1024x692.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F24173232%2FAhmedabad_riots1-300x203.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F24173232%2FAhmedabad_riots1.jpg%201184w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-637477%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22568%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20skyline%20of%20Ahmedabad%2C%20Gujarat%2C%20filled%20with%20smoke%20as%20buildings%20were%20set%20on%20fire%20by%20rioting%20mobs%20in%202002.%20Photo%3A%20Aksi%20great%2F%2FWikimedia%20Commons.%20CC%20BY-SA%203.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20mean%2C%20historians%20will%20pass%20a%20final%20judgement.%20These%20were%20all%20serious%20crises.%20Gujarat%20in%202002%2C%20Kashmir%20in%201989-90%20when%20the%20movement%20turned%20violently%20Islamic%20fundamentalist%20and%20the%20Pandits%20were%20purged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%20know%2C%20Punjab%20starting%20with%20Bhindranwale%20and%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20utterly%20ill-advised%20storming%20over%20the%20Golden%20Temple%20and%20so%20on.%20So%20these%20are%20all%20serious%20crises.%20I%E2%80%99m%20not%20saying%2C%20you%20know%2C%20you%20should%20discount%20the%20gravity%20of%20any%20of%20those%2C%20and%20it%20took%20us%20many%20years%20to%20recover%20from%20them%2C%20and%20sometimes%20we%20still%20haven%E2%80%99t%20fully%20recovered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20in%20that%20sense%2C%20that%20is%20why%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20history%20of%20states%20where%20there%20is%20inter-communal%20conflict%2C%20and%20the%20state%20and%20the%20government%20machinery%20either%20is%20apathetic%20or%20takes%20one%20side%2C%20and%20from%20that%20history%2C%20you%20see%20how%20much%20this%20has%20cost%20the%20Indian%20Republic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20makes%20it%20more%20urgent%20that%20proper%20action%20is%20taken%20by%20the%20union%20government%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20Manipur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Now%2C%20over%20the%20weekend%2C%20Ram%20Guha%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com.%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fmeiteis-begin-to-leave-mizoram-after-threat-manipur-govt-says-willing-to-provide-flights-8855091%2F%5C%22%3Ehundreds%20of%20Meitei%20fled%20Mizoram%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20a%20statement%20by%20the%20Mizo%20group%20PAMRA%20%5BPeace%20Accord%20MNF%20Returnees%E2%80%99%20Association%5D%2C%20advised%20them%20to%20leave%20Mizoram%20for%20their%20own%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAre%20you%20worried%20that%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20in%20Manipur%20is%20now%20having%20dangerous%20ripple%20effects%20through%20the%20Northeast%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Just%20a%E2%80%A6%20Again%2C%20an%20important%20correction%20to%20your%20statement.%20Hundreds%20of%20Meiteis%20have%20fled%20Mizoram%2C%20and%20prior%20to%20that%2C%20thousands%20of%20Kukis%20fled%20Manipur%20for%20Mizoram.%20So%20Kukis%20felt%20unsafe%20in%20Manipur.%20So%20they%20went%20across%20the%20border%2C%20where%20they%20felt%20the%20Mizos%20%E2%80%93%20with%20whom%20they%20have%20close%20ethnic%20ties%20%E2%80%93%20would%20protect%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20Mizoram%2C%20who%20actually%20has%20been%20very%20magnanimous%2C%20even%20in%20giving%20refuge%20to%20migrants%20across%20the%20border%2C%20I%20think%20is%20very%20admirable.%20He%20was%20not%20supported%20by%20the%20central%20government.%20He%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98please%20give%20me%20money%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t%20listen%20to%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20of%20course%2C%20we%20will%20have%20this%20counter-reaction%20in%20Mizoram%20where%20the%20Meiteis%20are%20seen%20as%20causing%20the%20fleeing%20of%20Kukis%20from%20Manipur%20to%20their%20state%2C%20which%20is%20already%20a%20vulnerable%20and%20overburdened%20state.%20So%20you%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20stuff%2C%20some%20of%20it%20is%20happening%20in%20Meghalaya.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20all%20of%20this%2C%20I%20mean%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20like%E2%80%A6%20I%20think%20I%20would%20%E2%80%93%20again%20this%20is%20hoping%20against%20hope%20%E2%80%93%20I%20hope%2C%20I%20would%20still%20wish%2C%20for%20the%20state%20of%20Manipur%20and%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20India%2C%20that%20the%20prime%20minister%20comes%20to%20parliament%20tomorrow%2C%20makes%20a%20statement%20and%20then%20listens%20to%20what%20the%20Opposition%20has%20to%20say%2C%20without%20heckling%20by%20the%20BJP%20party%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20that%20day%2C%20tomorrow%20or%20day%20after%20or%20any%20time%20soon%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%20is%20sacked.%20And%20an%20all-party%20delegation%20is%20sent%20to%20Manipur.%20You%20will%20recall%2C%20in%20the%20days%20when%20there%20were%20troubles%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20Manmohan%20Singh%2C%20Narasimha%20Rao%2C%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20were%20quite%20happy%2C%20and%20in%20fact%20encouraged%2C%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20democracy%2C%20all-party%20delegations%20and%20meetings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20here%2C%20there%20have%20been%20people%20waiting%20for%20weeks%20to%20see%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20he%20won%E2%80%99t%20give%20an%20audience.%20At%20all.%20You%20know%2C%20so%20it%20is%20not%20conduct%20becoming%20of%20a%20prime%20minister%2C%20let%20alone%20a%20prime%20minister%20who%20claims%20he%E2%80%99s%20very%20popular%2C%20who%20claims%20he%E2%80%99s%20a%20world%20leader%2C%20who%20has%20300%20odd%20seats%20in%20parliament.%20And%20yet%20he%E2%80%99s%20so%20weak%20and%20cowardly%20to%20address%20that%20same%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Just%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20the%20audience%2C%20I%20will%20point%20out%20that%20the%20ripple%20effects%20are%20now%20also%20beginning%20to%20worry%20the%20government%20in%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reports%20that%20the%20authorities%20in%20Assam%20are%20deeply%20concerned%20that%20some%20of%20the%20weaponry%20and%20guns%20looted%20or%20taken%20over%20by%20militants%20in%20Manipur%20could%20have%20reached%20Assam%2C%20and%20possibly%20into%20the%20hands%20of%20ULFA%20%5BUnited%20Liberation%20Front%20of%20Asom%5D.%20That%20is%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20the%20ripples%20of%20Manipur%20are%20spreading%20through%20the%20Northeast.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Well%2C%20you%E2%80%99re%20referencing%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20in%20Assam.%20Allow%20me%20to%20say%20that%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20Assam%20chief%20minister%20has%20also%20been%20unbecoming.%20You%20know%2C%20he%20has%20polarised%20things%2C%20he%E2%80%99d%20made%20all%20kinds%20of%20accusations%20against%20the%20UPA%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncidentally%2C%20there%20was%20a%20major%20incident%20in%20Manipur%20and%20protests%20by%20women%20against%20AFSPA%20and%20alleged%20violence%20on%20citizens%20by%20security%20forces.%20Manmohan%20Singh%20actually%20went%20to%20Imphal%2C%20you%20know.%20A%20year%20after%20that%2C%20but%20he%20went.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20I%20think%20for%20the%20Assam%20chief%20minister%2C%20who%20is%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20point%20man%20in%20the%20Northeast%2C%20to%20make%20more%20inflammatory%20statements%20as%20he%E2%80%99s%20been%20doing%2C%20including%20in%20his%20own%20state%2C%20about%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%20and%20so%20on%2C%20I%20think%20the%20whole%E2%80%A6%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20what%20they%20think.%20They%20are%20happy%20to%20sacrifice%20peace%2C%20stability%2C%20the%20future%20of%20India%20to%20win%20an%20election%20by%20making%20Hindus%20insecure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20mean%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20election%20plan%20in%202024%2C%20as%20it%20was%20in%202019%20(particularly%2C%20not%20so%20much%20in%202014)%2C%20is%20if%2060%25%20of%20Hindus%20vote%20for%20us%2C%20we%20will%20win.%20And%20what%E2%80%99s%20the%20way%3F%20By%20making%20them%20fearful%2C%20hateful%2C%20parano