%2Fbritish-mother-of-10-among-three-killed-in-motorway-crash-in-france-reports-12931393%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fbritish-mother-of-10-among-three-killed-in-motorway-crash-in-france-reports-12931393%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2267%25%20Indians%20Have%20Negative%20Opinion%20About%20China%2C%20the%20Highest%20Among%2024%20Surveyed%20Countries%3A%20Pew%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F07085318%2FChina-india.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20median%20of%2067%25%20of%20adults%20in%2024%20countries%20expressed%20unfavorable%20views%20about%20China%2C%20with%20India%20and%20Brazil%20having%20seen%20the%20highest%20increase%20in%20negative%20opinion%20about%20the%20Asian%20giant%2C%20a%20new%20Pew%20Research%20survey%20has%20shown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fglobal%2F2023%2F07%2F27%2Fchinas-approach-to-foreign-policy-gets-largely-negative-reviews-in-24-country-survey%2F%3Forg%3D982%26amp%3Blvl%3D100%26amp%3Bite%3D12306%26amp%3Blea%3D2626848%26amp%3Bctr%3D0%26amp%3Bpar%3D1%26amp%3Btrk%3Da0D3j000014BjciEAC%5C%22%3EThe%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20released%20last%20Friday%2C%20is%20based%20on%20phone%20and%20in-person%20surveys%20of%20around%2030%2C000%20people%20in%2024%20countries%20surveyed%20between%20February%20and%20May%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20that%20survey%2C%20it%20was%20found%20that%20a%20median%20of%2067%25%20stated%20that%20they%20had%20a%20negative%20view%20of%20China.%20Further%2C%20a%20median%20of%2071%25%20think%20that%20China%20does%20not%20contribute%20to%20global%20peace%20and%20stability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20even%20higher%20median%20of%2076%25%20of%20people%20believe%20that%20China%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20take%20into%20account%20the%20interest%20of%20their%20countries%2C%20while%20a%20median%20of%2057%25%20say%20that%20Beijing%20interferes%20in%20the%20internal%20affair%20of%20other%20countries%20to%20a%20fair%20amount.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20high-income%20countries%2C%20the%20negative%20opinions%20among%20the%20population%20range%20from%2050%25%20in%20Hungary%20and%20Spain%20to%2087%25%20in%20Australia%20and%20Japan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20among%20the%20eight%20middle-income%20countries%20surveyed%2C%20a%20majority%20in%20Kenya%2C%20Mexico%20and%20Nigeria%20even%20gave%20China%20a%20positive%20rating.%20India%20was%20the%20only%20middle-income%20country%20where%20the%20majority%20at%2067%25%20had%20unfavourable%20views%20about%20China%2C%20followed%20by%20Brazil%20at%2048%25%20and%20South%20Africa%20at%2040%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20global%20south%20%E2%80%93%20and%20even%20across%20the%20globe%2C%20India%20was%20marked%20out%20in%20the%20survey%20for%20the%20sharp%20downturn%20in%20views%20about%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNegative%20views%20in%20India%20rose%20from%2046%25%20in%202019%20to%2067%25%20in%202023.%20During%20this%20same%20time%20period%2C%20a%20conflict%20along%20the%20India-China%20border%20has%20repeatedly%20flared%20up%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20a%20rise%20of%2021%20percentage%20points%20in%20four%20years.%20The%20only%20other%20country%20to%20record%20a%20similarly%20steep%20increase%20of%2021%20percentage%20points%20in%20negative%20opinion%20about%20China%20is%20Brazil%2C%20from%20a%20low%20of%2025%25%20in%202017%20to%2048%25%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExcluding%202023%2C%20the%20recent%20annual%20surveys%20done%20in%20India%20show%20that%20the%20number%20of%20Indians%20who%20responded%20that%20they%20had%20an%20unfavourable%20view%20of%20China%20was%20usually%20less%20than%2050%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20there%20had%20been%20a%20downswing%20in%20negative%20opinion%20about%20China%20from%2041%25%20in%202013%20to%2032%25%20in%202015.%20This%20period%20seems%20to%20have%20coincided%20with%20an%20outreach%20to%20China%20with%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20hosted%20on%20the%20banks%20of%20Sabarmati%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%202014%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20Indian%20leader%20travelling%20to%20Beijing%20in%20May%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20negative%20opinion%20about%20China%20in%20India%20started%20to%20climb%20throughout%20the%202016%2C%202017%20and%202019%20surveys.%20The%20Pew%20Research%20Centre%20had%20not%20surveyed%20the%20eight%20middle-income%20countries%20since%202019%20due%20to%20the%20covid-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20troops%20came%20face-to-face%20over%20China%20building%20a%20road%20on%20territory%20claimed%20by%20Bhutan.%20The%20nine-week%20stand-off%20was%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fsa%3DD%26q%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fdoklam-stand-off-ends-india-china-troop-disengagement-begins%26ust%3D1690905720000000%26usg%3DAOvVaw3lVUxaejpezdnV2FZk8f-F%26hl%3Den%26source%3Dgmail%5C%22%3Eresolved%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20with%20both%20sides%20withdrawing%20their%20troops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThereafter%2C%20the%20stand-off%20at%20various%20points%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20in%20eastern%20Ladakh%20began%20in%20May%202022%2C%20which%20led%20to%2020%20Indian%20soldiers%20and%20at%20least%20four%20Chinese%20soldiers%20being%20killed%20in%20the%20first%20fatal%20clash%20at%20the%20border%20in%20four%20decades.%20While%20disengagement%20has%20taken%20place%20at%20some%20points%2C%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20soldiers%20continued%20to%20face%20off%20at%20Depsang%20and%20Demchok.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20the%20survey%20found%20that%20the%20confidence%20in%20the%20Chinese%20President%20%E2%80%9Cto%20do%20the%20right%20thing%20regarding%20world%20affairs%E2%80%9D%20is%20low%2C%20with%20the%20exception%20of%20African%20nations.%20Among%20the%20mid-income%20countries%2C%20the%20ratings%20for%20President%20Xi%20have%20worsened%20per%20se%20compared%20to%20their%20last%20survey%20of%202019.%20The%20share%20of%20those%20with%20little%20to%20no%20confidence%20in%20Xi%20went%20up%20by%2021%20percentage%20points%20in%20the%20last%20four%20years%20in%20India%2C%20followed%20by%20Mexico%20(17)%2C%20Brazil%20(15%20points)%2C%20Argentina%20(12%20points)%20and%20Nigeria%20(10%20points).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20survey%2C%20around%20a%20third%20of%20the%20people%20questioned%20in%2024%20countries%20see%20China%20as%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20leading%20economic%20power%2C%20with%20most%20including%20all%20middle-income%20countries%20giving%20that%20title%20to%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20at%20least%20half%20in%20most%20of%20the%20eight%20middle-income%20countries%20say%20that%20investment%20from%20China%20has%20benefited%20their%20country%E2%80%99s%20economy.%20But%2C%20Indians%20were%20again%20the%20most%20sceptical%2C%20with%2040%25%20asserting%20that%20Chinese%20investment%20has%20not%20helped%20the%20domestic%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20is%20a%20disparity%20in%20views%20about%20China%20across%20high-income%20and%20middle-income%20countries%2C%20there%20are%20also%20similarities%20that%20run%20across%20the%2024%20countries.%20%E2%80%9CA%20median%20of%2069%25%20describe%20China%E2%80%99s%20technological%20achievements%20as%20the%20best%20or%20above%20average%20relative%20to%20other%20wealthy%20nations%2C%20with%20similar%20shares%20in%20high-%20and%20middle-income%20countries.%20A%20median%20of%2054%25%20also%20see%20China%E2%80%99s%20military%20as%20among%20the%20best%20in%20the%20world%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20answer%20to%20additional%20questions%20about%20Chinese%20technological%20products%20in%20the%20eight%20middle-income%20countries%2C%20a%20median%20of%2062%25%20said%20that%20Chinese%20technology%20was%20well-made.%20In%20India%2C%2052%25%20said%20that%20Chinese%20tech%