ed%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20Encounter%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20family%20of%20Amir%20was%20also%20paid%20a%20compensation%20of%20Rs%205%20lakh%20by%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20government%20on%20July%2021%2C%20after%20they%20filed%20a%20contempt%20petition%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20against%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20government%20for%20not%20implementing%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20directions%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELateef%20says%20they%20are%20struggling%20to%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20death%20of%20his%20son.%20%E2%80%9CHis%20death%20has%20completely%20shattered%20us.%20We%20cannot%20believe%20that%20he%20is%20dead.%20His%20mother%20has%20been%20unwell%20after%20his%20death%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20vouches%20for%20the%20innocence%20of%20his%20son%20Amir.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20son%20was%20innocent%20and%20did%20not%20even%20have%20a%20remote%20link%20with%20militancy.%20I%20fail%20to%20understand%20why%20police%20declared%20him%20as%20militant%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%20that%20he%20will%20do%20whatever%20is%20possible%20to%20erase%20the%20%E2%80%9Clabel%E2%80%9D%20of%20militancy%20on%20his%20dead%20son.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20fought%20against%20militants%2C%20my%20son%20cannot%20be%20a%20militant.%20He%20was%20working%20as%20a%20helper%20at%20the%20office%20of%20Dr.%20Mudasir%20Gul%2C%20who%20was%20also%20killed%20in%20the%20shootout%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Magrey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJ%26amp%3BK%20Police%20had%20said%20that%20Amir%20was%20a%20close%20aide%20of%20a%20Pakistani%20militant%20killed%20in%20the%20shootout%20and%20his%20activities%20showed%20that%20he%2C%20too%2C%20was%20a%20militant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20an%20easy%20battle%20for%20Lateef%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELateef%20says%20that%20it%20was%20not%20an%20easy%20battle%20for%20him.%20%E2%80%9COn%20November%2016%2C%202021%2C%20I%20heard%20that%20my%20son%20was%20killed.%20I%20immediately%20rushed%20to%20Srinagar%20and%20sought%20his%20body%20but%20officials%20told%20me%20that%20he%20has%20already%20been%20buried%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELateef%20later%20approached%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir%20high%20court%20to%20seek%20the%20body%20of%20his%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20May%2027%2C%202022%2C%20a%20single%20bench%20of%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20high%20court%20directed%20the%20administration%20of%20the%20Union%20territory%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fhyderpora-encounter-aamir-magray-court-exhume%5C%22%3Eto%20exhume%20the%20body%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20arrange%20for%20its%20transportation%20to%20his%20native%20village%20in%20Ramban%20district.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fhyderpora-encounter-aamir-magray-court-exhume%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Want%20to%20Bring%20Him%20Home%E2%80%99%3A%20HC%20Allows%20Family%20of%20Man%20Killed%20in%20Hyderpora%20Encounter%20to%20Exhume%20Body%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20said%20that%20the%20state%20should%20also%20pay%20compensation%20of%20Rs%205%20lakh%20to%20his%20father%20for%20%E2%80%9Cdeprivation%20of%20his%20right%20to%20have%20the%20dead%20body%20of%20his%20son%20and%20give%20him%20decent%20burial%20as%20per%20family%20traditions%2C%20religious%20obligations%2C%20and%20faith%20which%20the%20deceased%20professed%20when%20he%20was%20alive%2C%E2%80%9D%20if%20it%20was%20not%20in%20a%20deliverable%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202022%2C%20a%20division%20bench%20of%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20high%20court%20said%20the%20plea%20for%20the%20exhumation%20of%20the%20body%20for%20%E2%80%9Cperformance%20of%20last%20rights%E2%80%9D%20was%20%E2%80%9Cunacceptable%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20it%20upheld%20the%20single%20Bench%E2%80%99s%20directive%20for%20compensation%20of%20Rs%205%20lakh%20to%20the%20family.%20It%20also%20asked%20the%20government%20to%20allow%20a%20maximum%20of%2010%20family%20members%20of%20Amir%20Magray%20to%20perform%20some%20last%20rituals%20at%20the%20Wadder%20Payeen%20graveyard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmir%E2%80%99s%20family%20challenged%20the%20division%20bench%20order%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20September%2011%2C%202022%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20dismissed%20the%20family%E2%80%99s%20plea%20for%20the%20exhumation%20of%20the%20body%2C%20saying%20there%20was%20nothing%20to%20show%20that%20the%20deceased%20was%20not%20given%20a%20decent%20burial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%2C%20however%2C%20ordered%20the%20administration%20to%20pay%20Rs%205%20lakh%20compensation%20to%20the%20family%20of%20the%20deceased%20and%20allow%20them%20to%20offer%20prayers%20at%20the%20grave%20of%20Magrey%20in%20line%20with%20the%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir%20high%20court%20orders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20advocate%20Deepika%20Pushkar%20Nath%2C%20Magrey%E2%80%99s%20counsel%2C%20said%20that%20they%20had%20filed%20a%20contempt%20petition%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20a%20few%20months%20ago%20against%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20government%20for%20disobedience%20of%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20we%20filed%20a%20contempt%20petition%2C%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20government%20paid%20compensation%20of%20Rs%205%20lakh%20to%20the%20family%20and%20also%20allowed%20them%20to%20offer%20prayers%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20for%20the%20first%20time%20that%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20government%20has%20paid%20compensation%20in%20such%20a%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690806959000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F03185603%2Fimage-2021-12-03T185548.753.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Frelieved-father-who-offered-prayers-at-sons-grave-19-months-after-the-hyderpora-shootout%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20family%20of%20Amir%20Magrey%2C%20who%20was%20killed%20in%20the%20shootout%2C%20had%20to%20wage%20a%20long-drawn%20legal%20battle%20to%20know%20where%20he%20was%20buried.%20His%20father%20now%20says%20he%20will%20do%20'whatever%20possible%20to%20erase%20the%20label%20of%20militancy'%20on%20his%20dead%20son.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Frelieved-father-who-offered-prayers-at-sons-grave-19-months-after-the-hyderpora-shootout%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Music%20declared%20immoral%20in%20Afghanistan%20by%20Taliban%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690806240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F07%2F70x70%2Fskynews-taliban-afghanistan_6236069.jpg%3F20230731132328%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Finstruments-thrown-on-fire-as-taliban-declares-music-immoral-in-afghanistan-12931238%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Musical%20instruments%20have%20been%20thrown%20on%20a%20bonfire%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20with%20the%20ruling%20Taliban%20government%20declaring%20music%20is%20immoral.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A564%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Finstruments-thrown-on-fire-as-taliban-declares-music-immoral-in-afghanistan-12931238%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Finstruments-thrown-on-fire-as-taliban-declares-music-immoral-in-afghanistan-12931238%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Finstruments-thrown-on-fire-as-taliban-declares-music-immoral-in-afghanistan-12931238%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kavita%20Singh's%20Inspiring%20Research%20%E2%80%93%20and%20Memories%20of%20Her%20Unwavering%20Kindness%20%E2%80%93%20Will%20Live%20On%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F31170005%2Fkavita-singh-lead-pic.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EInspirational%2C%20large-hearted%2C%20rigorous%2C%20lucid%2C%20deft%20narrator%20with%20the%20gift%20of%20elegant%20formulations%20%E2%80%93%20these%20are%20some%20of%20the%20adjectives%20that%20art%20historian%2C%20writer%20and%20curator%2C%20Professor%20Kavita%20Singh%2C%20garnered%20during%20her%20two-decade%20career%20as%20a%20teacher%20at%20the%20School%20of%20Arts%20and%20Aesthetics%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University.%20Two%20decades%20in%20which%20she%20made%20a%20name%20for%20herself%20through%20her%20path-breaking%20work%20in%20the%20area%20of%20Indian%20painting%20and%20especially%20museum%20studies%2C%20examining%20the%20politics%20underpinning%20the%20role%20of%20the%20latter%20as%20cultural%20institutions%20in%20colonial%20and%20post-colonial%20times.%20Nurturing%20a%20vast%20community%20of%20students%20from%20the%20MFA%20programme%20to%20the%20stage%20of%20M%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EPhil%20and%20PhD%20in%20the%20process.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOn%20July%2030%2C%20after%20putting%20up%20a%20spirited%20fight%20against%20cancer%20for%20about%20two%20years%2C%20the%20former%20professor%20and%20dean%20of%20the%20School%2C%20who%20received%20the%20Infosys%20Prize%202018%20for%20Humanities%2C%20breathed%20her%20last.%20She%20was%2058.%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CJust%20two%20weeks%20ago%2C%20she%20gave%20such%20a%20brilliant%20talk%20at%20the%20India%20Habitat%20Centre%2C%20that%20I%20unfortunately%20missed%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%20remembers%20friend%20and%20colleague%2C%20Prof%20Shukla%20Sawant%20ruefully.%20She%20has%20known%20Kavita%20for%20over%20three%20decades%20%E2%80%93%20starting%20off%20as%20teacher-student%20(Kavita%20the%20teacher%2C%20Shukla%20the%20student%2C%20both%20almost%20the%20same%20age)%2C%20becoming%20friends%20and%20later%20colleagues%20at%20the%20SAA%20from%20its%20inception.%20In%20her%20remembrance%20below%2C%20as%20told%20to%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Wire%3Cem%3E%2C%20art%20practitioner%20and%20teacher%20Shukla%20Sawant%20remembers%20Kavita%20Singh%20the%20person%2C%20the%20multi-faceted%20professional%2C%20and%20the%20core%20of%20unshakeable%20integrity%20and%20quest%20that%20defined%20her.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20met%20Kavita%20in%201987.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20had%20just%20completed%20her%20Master%20of%20Fine%20Art%20(MFA)%20programme%20from%20MS%20University%2C%20Baroda%20(at%20that%20time%2C%20only%20a%20small%20number%20of%20universities%20offered%20post%20graduate%20degrees%20in%20studio%20practice%20or%20a%20specialised%20research%20degree%20in%20art%20history).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20had%20joined%20the%20newly%20instituted%20MFA%20programme%20at%20the%20College%20of%20Art%2C%20Delhi%2C%20after%20a%20stint%20of%20studying%20lithography%20at%20the%20Ecole%20des%20Beaux-Arts%2C%20Paris%2C%20and%20we%20had%20no%20one%20to%20teach%20us%20art%20history.%20It%20was%20Kavita%20who%20came%20to%20teach%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERather%2C%20we%20students%20had%20come%20to%20know%20of%20her%20and%20we%20literally%20chose%20her%20as%20our%20art%20history%20teacher!%20She%20was%20part%20of%20the%20Triveni%20Kala%20Sangam-Mandi%20House%20art%20world%2C%20not%20far%20from%20our%20college%2C%20where%20people%20associated%20with%20the%20arts%20would%20socialise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20had%20never%20studied%20art%20history%20systematically%20before%20that.%20I%20have%20a%20distinct%20memory%20of%20sitting%20on%20the%20College%20of%20Art%20lawn%2C%20with%20Kavita%20in%20her%20best%20performative%20manner%20taking%20a%20class%20on%20symbolism.%20All%20of%20us%2C%20steeped%20in%20modernism%2C%20only%20understood%20symbolism%20as%20a%2019th%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%93%3C%2Fspan%3Ecentury%20art%20movement%20in%20France%2C%20but%20she%20was%20trying%20to%20explain%20to%20us%20the%20larger%20idea%20of%20what%20symbolism%20meant.%20We%20students%20just%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20her.%20She%20was%20our%20age%2C%20actually%20a%20year%20younger%20than%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20paths%20kept%20crossing%2C%20because%20the%20art%20world%20was%20very%20small%20at%20that%20point.%20After%20my%20MFA%2C%20I%20started%20teaching%20at%20Jamia%20Millia.%20Kavita%20joined%20the%20National%20Institute%20of%20Fashion%20Technology%20as%20faculty%20and%20then%20pursued%20her%20PhD%20at%20Punjab%20University%2C%20Chandigarh%2C%20where%20she%20was%20a%20student%20of%20Prof%20B.N.%20Goswamy.%20She%20was%20very%20clear%20that%20she%20did%20not%20want%20to%20do%20her%20PhD%20abroad%2C%20because%20here%20was%20the%20finest%20scholar%20of%20Indian%20miniatures%2C%20and%20Chandigarh%20with%20its%20rich%20wealth%20of%20museums%20was%20right%20next%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20came%20our%20London%20sojourn%20later%20in%20the%201990s.%20Kavita%20had%20a%20Nehru%20Trust%20fellowship%20to%20research%20at%20the%20Victoria%20and%20Albert%20Museum%20and%20I%20was%20at%20the%20Slade%20School%20of%20Art%20on%20a%20Commonwealth%20scholarship.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20time%20we%20were%20using%20email%20to%20communicate%20with%20people%20in%20India.%20Kavita%20would%20come%20over%20to%20use%20email%20at%20Slade%20School%20because%20the%20V%26amp%3BA%20museum%20did%20not%20have%20a%20computer%20lab.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20explored%20London%20together.%20Besides%2C%20she%20was%20a%20fantastic%20cook.%20I%20remember%20a%20lively%20lunch%20gathering%20at%20her%20sublet%20in%20Camden%20for%20which%20she%20cooked%20the%20most%20amazing%20meal.%20If%20I%20remember%20correctly%2C%20Subba%20Ghosh%20my%20contemporary%20at%20the%20College%20of%20Art%20and%20Slade%20School%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20novelist%20Ruchir%20Joshi%20were%20also%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20the%20time%20when%20Kavita%20became%20interested%20in%20museum%20collections%20and%20the%20phenomenon%20of%20the%20colonial%20museum.%20For%20us%20it%20was%20all%20completely%20new%2C%20for%20critical%20museum%20studies%20as%20a%20disciplinary%20field%20barely%20existed%20in%20India%20at%20the%20time.%20She%20would%20tell%20us%20all%20these%20fascinating%20details%20about%20how%20different%20museums%20across%20the%20world%20had%20come%20into%20being%20%E2%80%93%20Ananda%20Coomaraswamy%20was%20someone%20she%20was%20looking%20at%20closely%20%E2%80%93%20and%20right%20after%20that%20she%20got%20the%20Asia%20Society%20fellowship%20and%20went%20off%20to%20New%20York.%20I%20returned%20to%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20both%20of%20us%20ended%20up%20getting%20a%20job%20at%20the%20School%20of%20Arts%20and%20Aesthetics%20that%20had%20just%20been%20set%20up%20at%20the%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%20(JNU).%20This%20was%20in%202001.%20It%20was%20a%20great%20opportunity%20to%20start%20from%20scratch.%20There%20were%20five%20of%20us%20%E2%80%93%20Jyotindra%20Jain%2C%20Kavita%20and%20I%20specialised%20in%20visual%20studies%2C%20and%20H.S.%20Shivaprakash%20and%20Bishnupriya%20Dutt%20in%20theatre%20studies%2C%20and%20we%20were%20given%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20to%20set%20up%20the%20entire%20programme.%20We%20worked%20out%20of%20one%20room%20for%20the%20first%20two%20years%2C%20even%20got%20the%20building%20built%2C%20furnished%20and%20equipped%20with%20appropriate%20audio-visual%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F31170126%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-31-at-4.53.22-PM.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F31170126%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-31-at-4.53.22-PM.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F31170126%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-31-at-4.53.22-PM-300x217.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F31170126%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-31-at-4.53.22-PM-1024x741.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-665999%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22868%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EKavita%20Singh%20with%20students%20of%20the%20first%20MA%20in%20Arts%20and%20Aesthetics%20interdisciplinary%20programme%20of%20SAA%2C%202003.%20Singh%20is%20in%20the%20right%20corner.%20Photo%3A%20Special%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20comprised%20the%20first%20generation%20of%20teachers%20using%20computers%2C%20CDs%20and%20projectors%20to%20teach%20art%20history%2C%20unlike%20those%20earlier%2C%20who%20used%20analogue%20slides%20or%20books.%20We%20all%20had%20to%20get%20acquainted%20with%20the%20technology.%20Kavita%20was%20completely%20comfortable%20with%20technology%2C%20actually%20on%20top%20of%20it%2C%20and%20could%20get%20any%20machine%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20approach%20was%20decided%20by%20a%20couple%20of%20factors.%20Most%20art%20institutions%20in%20India%20were%20of%20colonial%20vintage%20%E2%80%93%20the%20exceptions%20being%20the%20Fine%20Arts%20Faculty%2C%20MS%20University%2C%20Baroda%20(1950s)%20and%20Chitrakala%20Parishad%2C%20Bangalore%20(1960s).%20Also%2C%2090%25%20of%20what%20was%20produced%20in%20the%20visual%20field%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20by%20people%20who%20studied%20in%20art%20schools.%20So%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20create%20a%20theoretical%20programme%2C%20starting%20with%20an%20interdisciplinary%20programme%20which%20still%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETeaching%20in%20JNU%20was%20a%20learning%20experience%20as%20well.%20The%20students%20came%20from%20diverse%20social%20and%20economic%20backgrounds%20because%20of%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20highly%20regarded%20deprivation%20point%20system.%20It%20was%20a%20university%20that%20attracted%20students%20from%20all%20over%20the%20world%20as%20well.%20We%20had%20to%20reckon%20with%20our%20own%20prejudices%20and%20course%20correct%20repeatedly%2C%20and%20having%20student%20representation%20in%20Boards%20of%20Studies%20and%20as%20members%20of%20Academic%20Councils%20was%20immensely%20helpful.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOurs%20was%20a%20small%20faculty%20initially%2C%20and%20despite%20the%20vast%20temporal%20and%20geographical%20span%20of%20the%20core%20areas%20of%20Art%20History%2C%20we%20had%20to%20teach%20everything.%20That%20meant%20learning%20to%20teach%20in%20an%20inter-disciplinary%20way%20(cinema%20studies%20came%20later).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20level%20of%20Kavita%E2%80%99s%20rigour%20was%20new%20to%20me%20as%20I%20was%20a%20practitioner%20and%20did%20not%20come%20from%20an%20art%20history%20background.%20It%20meant%20reading%20all%20the%20time%20and%20translating%20the%20material%20into%20appropriate%20power%20point%20slides.%20For%20Kavita%2C%20Mughal%20painting%20was%20an%20area%20of%20passion.%20The%20courses%20she%20taught%20were%20on%20Indian%20painting%2C%20but%20her%20research%20interest%20lay%20in%20museum%20studies.%20This%20was%20a%20new%20way%20of%20looking%20at%20what%20the%20museum%20meant%20in%20its%20journey%20from%20a%20colonial%20to%20a%20post-colonial%20context.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20completely%20upturned%20the%20belief%20that%20museums%20are%20neutral%20spaces%20of%20display.%20Even%20her%20students%20have%20gone%20on%20to%20produce%20amazing%20analysis%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20the%20National%20Gallery%20of%20Modern%20Art%20or%20the%20National%20Museum%20and%20many%20others.%20The%20politics%20of%20collecting%2C%20the%20whims%20and%20fancies%20of%20collectors%20%E2%80%93%20why%20they%20collect%20what%20they%20collect%20%E2%80%93%20was%20an%20important%20area%20of%20concern.%20Kavita%20worked%20very%20closely%20with%20Tapati%20Guha%20Thakurta%2C%20a%20leading%20scholar%20of%20museum%20studies.%20They%20had%20similar%20interests%20and%20did%20many%20projects%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20extremely%20lucid%20writer%20and%20a%20performative%20speaker%20who%20had%20you%20hooked%2C%20Kavita%20could%20do%20a%20quick%20reading%20of%20a%20text%20and%20distil%20its%20essence.%20She%20would%20also%20describe%20painting%20in%20great%20detail%2C%20literally%20scrutinising%20a%20painting%20square%20inch%20by%20square%20inch.%20The%20fact%20that%20she%20was%20a%20literature%20student%20in%20BA%20(from%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Lady%20Shriram%20College)%20and%20knew%20how%20to%20narrativise%20art%20history%20was%20a%20great%20strength.%20She%20would%20tell%20me%20%E2%80%93%20I%20like%20to%20put%20art%20history%20into%20practice%20and%20curation%20is%20an%20important%20site%20of%20intervention.%20As%20a%20museum%20person%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20we%20do%2C%20we%20make%20these%20narratives%20come%20alive%20to%20the%20public.%20She%20saw%20her%20role%20as%20that%20of%20a%20public%20intellectual.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20her%20lectures%20are%20available%20on%20YouTube.%20In%20fact%2C%20I%20send%20their%20links%20to%20people%20as%20a%20way%20of%20learning%20how%20to%20structure%20a%20lecture.%20There%20would%20always%20be%20a%20build-up%2C%20with%20her%20holding%20back%20the%20bits%20that%20were%20the%20most%20enticing%20for%20later%2C%20keeping%20listeners%20hooked%20till%20the%20very%20end%20when%20she%20would%20reveal%20something%20magnificent.%20Every%20one%20of%20her%20lectures%20poses%20a%20question%2C%20or%20has%20an%20interesting%20perspective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOr%20take%20the%20practice%20of%20teaching%20art%20history%20through%20reproductions.%20We%20never%20get%20a%20sense%20of%20scale%20at%20all.%20Through%20Kavita%E2%80%99s%20wonderful%20power%20points%2C%20students%20would%20be%20able%20to%20see%20miniatures%20on%20a%20very%20large%20scale.%20The%20way%20she%20would%20arrange%20details%2C%20pulling%20out%20something%20she%20wanted%20students%20to%20see%2C%20brought%20the%20subject%20closer%20to%20her%20students.%20But%20she%20would%20also%20insist%20on%20museum%20visits%20to%20engage%20with%20works%20in%20all%20their%20miniature%2C%20material%20glory%20and%20critically%20scrutinise%20even%20the%20texts%20next%20to%20them%20on%20the%20walls%20for%20what%20they%20revealed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20in%20the%20initial%20years%20many%20students%20from%20the%20Centre%20for%20Historical%20Studies%20at%20JNU%20would%20take%20her%20course%20on%20Mughal%20and%20Rajput%20paintings%20and%20museum%20studies%2C%20then%20go%20abroad%20to%20specialise%20in%20art%20history.%20That%20too%20has%20happened.%20Our%20M.Phil%2C%20PhD%20took%20a%20while%20to%20take%20off%20and%20now%20%C2%A0offers%20%C2%A0specialised%20research%20degrees%2C%20%C2%A0in%20visual%20studies%2C%20theatre%20and%20performance%20studies%20or%20cinema%20studies.%20Kavita%20is%20leaving%20behind%20a%20number%20of%20scholars%20who%20have%20benefitted%20from%20her%20insightful%20research%20guidance.%20They%20are%20devasted%20by%20her%20departure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKavita%20had%20a%20way%20of%20involving%20her%20students%20in%20her%20various%20projects%2C%20especially%20her%20research%20into%20museums.%20So%2C%20many%20of%20them%20are%20now%20working%20on%20museum%20studies%20today%2C%20such%20as%20Deepti%20Mulgund%2C%20Akshay%20Tankha%2C%20Arnika%20Ahldag%20and%20Brinda%20Kumar.%20Many%20have%20literally%20travelled%20across%20the%20country%20mapping%20the%20history%20of%20museums%2C%20looking%20at%20what%20they%20were%20communicating%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20context.%20Were%20these%20institutions%20playing%20the%20same%20role%20as%20the%20museum%20in%20colonial%20times%20or%20was%20it%20any%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20what%20the%20phenomenal%20work%20that%20she%20co-edited%20with%20Saloni%20Mathur%20years%20later%2C%20%3Cem%3ENo%20Touching%2C%20No%20Spitting%2C%20No%20Praying%3A%20The%20Museum%20in%20South%20Asia%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Routledge%2C%202014)%2C%20was%20all%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20original%20work%20that%20comes%20to%20mind%20is%20Kavita%E2%80%99s%20Getty%20Research%20Institute%20Council%20Lecture%2C%20%E2%80%98Real%20Birds%20in%20Imagined%20Gardens%3A%20Mughal%20Painting%20Between%20Persia%20and%20Europe%E2%80%99%2C%20published%20in%202017.%20How%20elegantly%20she%20questioned%20the%20conventional%20linear%20arc%20of%20looking%20at%20Mughal%20painting%20by%20showing%C2%A0that%20Mughal%20painting%20had%20different%20phases%20of%20being%20in%20conversation%20with%20Persian%20and%20European%20styles%2C%20which%20sprang%20as%20much%20from%20court%20politics%20as%20from%20aesthetic%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20for%20her%20significant%20work%20in%20this%20area%20and%20in%20museum%20studies%20that%20she%20received%20the%20Infosys%20Prize%202018%20for%20Humanities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F31170328%2FKaviShukla.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F31170328%2FKaviShukla.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F31170328%2FKaviShukla-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F31170328%2FKaviShukla-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666001%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EShukla%20Sawant%20(L)%20and%20Kavita%20Singh.%20Photo%3A%20Special%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20just%20as%20a%20scholar%20and%20writer%2C%20Kavita%20was%20extremely%20dynamic%20in%20many%20respects.%20She%20would%20push%20people%20to%20do%20things%2C%20arrange%20conferences%20with%20international%20scholars%2C%20and%20ran%20several%20visiting%20scholar%20programmes%20supported%20by%20several%20international%20foundations.%20She%20was%20able%20to%20get%20substantial%20funding%20to%20build%20up%20the%20book%20collection%20of%20the%20School%20of%20Arts%20and%20Aesthetics%20and%20have%20scholars%20visit%20from%20across%20the%20world.%20She%20literally%20put%20the%20School%20of%20Arts%20and%20Aesthetics%20on%20the%20international%20map.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20that%20she%20has%20this%20huge%20group%20of%20students%20who%20specialised%C2%A0%20in%20various%20areas%20of%20Indian%20painting%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20Dipanwita%20Donde%2C%20who%20is%20working%20for%20the%20Max%20Weber%20Stiftung%20(MWF%20Delhi)%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20or%20Suryanandini%20Narian%20who%20looks%20at%20hand-painted%20photographs%20and%20now%20teaches%20in%20our%20school%20%E2%80%93%20speaks%20for%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20museum%20recruitments%20in%20India%2C%20it%20is%20largely%20civil%20servants%20who%20run%20the%20show%20instead%20of%20a%20professional%20cadre%20of%20museologists.%20You%20need%20professionals%2C%20not%20people%20who%20will%20abide%20by%20the%20existing%20regime%E2%80%99s%20view%20of%20the%20world.%20It%20is%20the%20private%20museums%20who%20are%20hiring%20museum%20professionals%20but%20even%20there%2C%20it%20is%20not%20done%20the%20way%20it%20is%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20world.%20Private%20museums%20remain%20largely%20personality%20driven%20with%20hagiographic%20goals%20rather%20than%20being%20run%20as%20academic%20institutions%20that%20offer%20critical%20insights%20into%20art%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20some%20government%20museum%20directors%20are%20able%20to%20activate%20these%20repositories%20but%20by%20and%20large%20their%20programmes%20shy%20away%20from%20any%20polemics%20and%20are%20therefore%20dry.%20They%20may%20collect%20material%20but%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20how%20to%20make%20that%20art%20history%20come%20alive%20and%20are%20too%20wary%20of%20ruffling%20feathers%20to%20provide%20meaningful%20insights.%20Instead%2C%20they%20tip%20into%20hypernationalistic%20narratives%20veering%20on%20fiction.%20This%20was%20a%20subject%20of%20great%20concern%20to%20Kavita.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20Kavita%20was%20a%20person%20of%20strong%20convictions%20about%20democratic%2C%20academic%20processes%20regarding%20how%20a%20university%20should%20run.%20For%20instance%2C%20when%20she%20became%20Dean%20of%20the%20School%20of%20Arts%20and%20Aesthetics%20in%202017%2C%20JNU%20was%20going%20through%20a%20particularly%20difficult%20period.%20M.%20Jagadesh%20Kumar%2C%20the%20then%20Vice%20Chancellor%20simply%20did%20not%20believe%20in%20participatory%2C%20institutional%20ways%20of%20functioning.%20Here%20was%20a%20dynamic%20and%20internationally%20renowned%20scholar%2C%20one%20among%20a%20handful%20of%20women%20who%20had%20held%20administrative%20positions%20in%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20history%2C%20whom%20he%20removed%20from%20deanship%20(in%202019)%20because%20she%20refused%20to%20endorse%20the%20fee%20hike%20that%20had%20been%20implemented%20without%20following%20the%20due%20process%20of%20deliberation%20and%20discussion%20through%20which%20JNU%20had%20functioned%20since%20it%20was%20established.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKavita%20fought%20these%20malpractices%20through%20the%20courts%20of%20law%20and%20won.%20That%20tells%20you%20a%20lot%20about%20the%20grit%20she%20possessed%2C%20how%20incredibly%20brave%20she%20was.%20In%20December%202022%2C%20she%20resigned%20from%20the%20SAA%20to%20face%20her%20illness%20with%20the%20same%20grit%20and%20courage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F31170223%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-31-at-4.55.43-PM.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F31170223%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-31-at-4.55.43-PM.jpeg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F31170223%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-31-at-4.55.43-PM-300x225.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666000%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EEntire%20SAA%20faculty%20at%20Kavita%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20December%202022%20farewell%20lunch.%20Photo%3A%20Special%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKavita%20had%20an%20active%20presence%20in%20so%20many%20circles%20that%20it%20opened%20up%20new%20ways%20of%20thinking%20and%20doing.%20She%20was%20able%20to%20harness%20the%20support%20of%20several%20international%20foundations%20because%20of%20which%20an%20array%20of%20international%20scholars%20have%20taught%20entire%20semesters%20at%20the%20School%20%E2%80%93%20John%20Clark%2C%20Griselda%20Pollock%2C%20Natalie%20Kampen%2C%20Avinoam%20Shalem%2C%20to%20name%20just%20a%20few.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKavita%20was%20academically%20very%20rigorous%20and%20insisted%20on%20implementing%20what%20she%20had%20initially%20learnt%20at%20MS%20University%20Baroda%2C%20once%20famed%20for%20its%20Art%20History%20Department.%20Later%2C%20through%20her%20various%20academic%20collaborations%2C%20she%20succeeded%20in%20opening%20doors%20for%20younger%20scholars%20to%20conduct%20high%20quality%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20the%20kind%20of%20scholar%2C%20colleague%20and%20friend%20everybody%20hopes%20for%20in%20their%20circle.%20How%20does%20one%20sum%20up%20the%20journey%20of%20someone%20like%20Kavita%2C%20a%20brilliant%20scholar%2C%20writer%2C%20curator%2C%20teacher%2C%20mentor%20and%20institution%20builder%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20yesterday%2C%20the%20one%20image%20that%20has%20been%20coming%20to%20mind%20is%20of%20our%20study%20tour%20to%20Lahore%20in%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20made%20possible%20by%20Salima%20Hashmi%2C%20the%20renowned%20Pakistani%20artist.%20This%20is%20when%20scholars%20across%20the%20border%20could%20actually%20engage%20in%20intellectual%20friendships%20without%20the%20fear%20of%20being%20blacklisted.%20I%20remember%20visiting%20the%20tomb%20of%20Nur%20Jehan%20with%20Kavita%2C%20looking%20at%20the%20breathtaking%20pietra%20dura%20work%20on%20the%20tomb%20and%20discussing%20the%20powerful%20role%20that%20women%20had%20played%20in%20supporting%20the%20arts.%20Kavita%20may%20have%20passed%20away%20physically%2C%20but%20all%20that%20she%20built%20will%20give%20immense%20pleasure%20to%20people%20for%20years%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAs%20told%20to%20The%20Wire.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690803585000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F31170005%2Fkavita-singh-lead-pic.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fthe-arts%2Fkavita-singhs-inspiring-research-and-memories-of-her-unwavering-kindness-will-live-on%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kavita%20Singh%20was%20a%20brilliant%20scholar%2C%20writer%2C%20curator%2C%20teacher%2C%20mentor%20and%20institution%20builder.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A119%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fthe-arts%2Fkavita-singhs-inspiring-research-and-memories-of-her-unwavering-kindness-will-live-on%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Girl%2C%2010%2C%20and%20her%20mum%20among%20five%20dead%20in%20Russian%20missile%20strike%20on%20Zelenskyy's%20home%20city%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690803300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F07%2F70x70%2Fskynews-missile-kryvyi-rih_6236099.jpg%3F20230731133834%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fukraine-war-girl-10-and-her-mother-among-five-dead-in-russian-missile-strike-on-president-volodymyr-zelenskyys-home-city-12931194%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Five%20people%2C%20including%20a%2010-year-old%20girl%20and%20her%20mother%2C%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20a%20Russian%20missile%20strike%20